AngularJS 

MVC - Model , view , Controller 

Model - Data
View - UI 
Controller - Interaction between model and view

AngularJS - Data Binding :
Synchronization of model and view part

two types - one way and two way data binding'

Oneway :

Data flows in one way from model to view 
- can use ng-bind or {{expression}}

-Model data combines with html to show the output for user


TwoWay:

Data flows in bidirectional , changes in VIEW will affect Model and Changes in MODEL affect View
- can use ng-model directive
- used in textbox , text area , select , buttons
-Event triggers at view side by users


AngularJS-Expressions

· AngularJS evaluates expression and bind the result with
HTML similar to Javascript
· Contains literals, operators, variables
· {{expression}}, ng-bind=expression
· Numbers, strings, objects, Arrays are used in expressions
. ng-app = " ", ng-app
· ng-init is used to initialize the variables
· cannot Contains loops, conditions, exceptions , functions,comma


AngularJS-Directives

. Extends the HTML element attributes
· Mostly start with ng-
. Contains many built-in directives
· Able to create and customize directives
. Can also start with x-, data-, : , _

-  Builtln Directives:

· ng-app
· ng-init
· ng-model 
· ng-bind
· ng-controller
. ng-repeat
· ng-readonly
· ng-disabled
· ng-if


AngularJS-Controller

. Controller is a JavaScript object contains properties and
functions
· Application data's are controlled by controllers
. Controllers manage the data between model and view
· $scope is used as parameter refers the module controlled by
the controller
· ng-controller directive is used
. Controllers can be stored as external files
